- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as Probability Smoothing is a core model for sequential prediction, which is a common task in machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the efficiency of the Probability Smoothing algorithm. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper analyzes the redundancy of Probability Smoothing. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as data compression algorithms can be used in cryptography and security applications.
